ccessful lives. Using ethnographic, survey, and interview data in two racially diverse, low-achieving high schools, Warikoo analyzes seemingly oppositional styles, tastes in music, and school behaviors and finds that most teens try to find a balance between success with peers and success in school.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAcademic achievementvCross-cultural studies. 0aAssimilation (Sociology) 0aAssimilation (Sociology). 0aChildren of immigrantsvCross-cultural studies. 0aGroup identityvCross-cultural studies. 0aHigh school studentsxSocial life and customsvCross-cultural studies. 0aYouthxSocial life and customsvCross-cultural studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094779540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947795423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520947795/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles